## Key Principles

- **Plan before building**: Use plan mode for non-trivial tasks, even when they look simple at first glance.
- **Replace, don't deprecate**: Remove old code. No backward-compat shims, re-exports, or `# removed` comments.
- **Capture lessons aggressively**: When you notice a correction, gotcha, pattern, or convention worth preserving, use `/learn` without hesitation. Bias toward capturing — pruning happens later via `/manage-lessons`.

## Git Workflow

- Never commit directly to main (enforced by hook).
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`, `chore/`, `docs/` prefixes.
- **User owns shared-state ops.** Claude does not merge to main, push, open pull requests, or push tags — branch work ends at handoff. `/draft-pr` is user-invoked: it writes the description, you open the PR. When merging directly, use `--no-ff` to preserve branch history.

## Toolkit

This project uses [claude-toolkit](https://github.com/hata/claude-toolkit) for Claude Code configuration.

- **Hooks**: `.claude/hooks/` — guardrails enforced automatically (dangerous commands, feature branch, secrets)
- **Skills**: `.claude/skills/` — run `/list-docs` to see available context, or invoke skills by name
- **Docs**: `.claude/docs/` — prescriptive rules and reference documentation loaded by session-start hook
- **Validation**: `make claude-toolkit-validate` — check configuration health
- **Sync**: `make claude-toolkit-sync` — pull latest toolkit updates
